<paragraph id="35A6E150E17C797B9A7A92CE63D2D833" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
This species showed higher values in the percentage of observations than the number of observations per grid cell. It is known mainly from the 
<normalizedToken id="5D9A0A549F37602F4E5D2931F5ED3890" originalValue="Buzkâ€™s">Buzk's</normalizedToken>
Gard National Nature Park and near Mykolaiv (
<bibRefCitation id="DAB49CA13034BA656F363F00E73162AA" author="Dotsenko, IB" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="109 - 120" refId="B16" refString="Dotsenko, IB, Radchenko, VI, 2005. The Herpetofauna of Antropogenous Landscapes of Nikolayev and Odessa Regions. Proceedings of the Zoological Museum 37: 109 - 120" title="The Herpetofauna of Antropogenous Landscapes of Nikolayev and Odessa Regions." volume="37" year="2005">Dotsenko and Radchenko 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="62B4434912E577D7F7EFD32F345BEDAE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/15685381-00002935" author="Sillero, N" journalOrPublisher="Amphibia-Reptilia" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 31" refId="B57" refString="Sillero, N, Campos, J, Bonardi, A, Corti, C, Creemers, R, Crochet, PA, Crnobrnja, JI, Denoel, M, Ficetola, GF, Goncalves, J, Kuzmin, S, Lymberakis, P, Pous, de P, Rodriguez, A, Sindaco, R, Speybroeck, J, Toxopeus, B, Vieites, DR, Vences, M, 2014. Updated distribution and biogeography of amphibians and reptiles of Europe. Amphibia-Reptilia 35: 1 - 31, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/15685381-00002935" title="Updated distribution and biogeography of amphibians and reptiles of Europe." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/15685381-00002935" volume="35" year="2014">Sillero et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DE23E72D5F4EA979C5A05DDDF357D737" author="Suriadna, NM" editor="Akimov, IA" journalOrPublisher="Fauna 2 (7). Druk Art, Chernivtsi" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="303 - 309" refId="B60" refString="Suriadna, NM, Mykytynets, GI, Manuilova, OM, 2018. Cadastre of registrations of some species of amphibians and reptiles of the south of Ukraine listed in the Red Book. In: Akimov, IA, Kharchenko, VO, Kostyushin, VA, Vasilyuk, OV, Eds., Materials for the 4th edition of the Red Book of Ukraine. Fauna 2(7). Druk Art, Chernivtsi: 303 - 309" title="Cadastre of registrations of some species of amphibians and reptiles of the south of Ukraine listed in the Red Book." volumeTitle="Materials for the 4 th edition of the Red Book of Ukraine." year="2018">Suriadna et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E6A4E2F8924659EA840ACD29E3ADF8C2" author="Mykytynets, GI" editor="Akimov, IA" journalOrPublisher="Fauna 3 (7). Druk Art, Chernivtsi" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="213 - 215" refId="B49" refString="Mykytynets, GI, Suriadna, NM, Markautsan, OE, Ivanov, OG, 2019. Findings of reptilian of the Red Book of southern Ukraine. In: Akimov, IA, Kharchenko, VO, Kostyushin, VA, Vasilyuk, OV, Eds., Materials for the 4th edition of the Red Book of Ukraine. Fauna 3(7). Druk Art, Chernivtsi: 213 - 215" title="Findings of reptilian of the Red Book of southern Ukraine." volumeTitle="Materials for the 4 th edition of the Red Book of Ukraine." year="2019">Mykytynets et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Some records were made in the Inhul River valley (north-eastern part of the Mykolaiv Oblast; 
<bibRefCitation id="7EF2BA334419515021DEA9271EBD3F0D" author="Dotsenko, IB" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="109 - 120" refId="B16" refString="Dotsenko, IB, Radchenko, VI, 2005. The Herpetofauna of Antropogenous Landscapes of Nikolayev and Odessa Regions. Proceedings of the Zoological Museum 37: 109 - 120" title="The Herpetofauna of Antropogenous Landscapes of Nikolayev and Odessa Regions." volume="37" year="2005">Dotsenko and Radchenko 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A5CC9EF44997489FF3F602BB696AD552" author="Nekrasova, OD" editor="Konishchuk, VV" journalOrPublisher="DIA, Kyiv" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="200 - 205" refId="B50" refString="Nekrasova, OD, 2013. Herpetofauna of Inhul River Park. In: Konishchuk, VV, Ed., Ecology of wetlands and peatlands. DIA, Kyiv: 200 - 205" title="Herpetofauna of Inhul River Park." volumeTitle="Ecology of wetlands and peatlands." year="2013">Nekrasova 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Most of our own records were along the valley of the Southern Bug River (from Pervomaisk to the estuary). The highest number of records were from 
<normalizedToken id="1F9AF7ED9BCEC05B3A3E294CDC2F8723" originalValue="Buzkâ€™s">Buzk's</normalizedToken>
Gard National Nature Park (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="786B1908B3E5EFD5BDC9A0079DC45089" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Representative habitats for the herpetofauna in the Mykolaiv Oblast: A. habitat of Coronella austriaca near the village of Zaichevsk; B. habitat of Zamenis longissimus near the village of Grushivka; C. habitat of Podarcis tauricus near the village of Trykhaty; D. Buzk's Gard National Nature Park. Photographs by V. Strenada (A), O. Oskyrko (B, C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/herpetozoa.34.e62459.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536310" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">10D</figureCitation>
). In contrast to the other lizards, we found this species often and in high numbers.
</paragraph>
